## Standardize column names across all attitude tables
att_list <- list(att1, att2, att3, att4, att5, att6, att7, att8) %>%
  lapply(function(df) {
    df <- df %>%
      rename(Frequency = ifelse("n" %in% names(df), "n", names(df)[3]),
             Percent   = ifelse(!("Percent" %in% names(df)), names(df)[4], "Percent"))
    return(df)
  })

# Combine all attitude subsections
attitude_table <- bind_rows(att_list) %>%
  select(Question, Response, Frequency, Percent)

make_map5 <- function(data, fill_var, title) {
  ggplot(data) +
    geom_sf(aes(fill = .data[[fill_var]]), color = "white", linewidth = 0.4) +
    coord_sf(datum = NA) +
    scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "plasma", direction = -1, na.value = "gray85") +
    geom_sf_text(aes(label = subcounty_clean),
                 size = 4, color = "black", fontface = "bold", check_overlap = TRUE) +
    labs(title = title) +
    theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
    theme(
      plot.background = element_rect(fill = "gray92", color = NA),
      panel.background = element_rect(fill = "gray92", color = NA),
      legend.background = element_rect(fill = "gray92", color = NA),
      legend.key = element_rect(fill = "gray92", color = NA),
      plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, color = "black"),
      legend.position = "bottom",
      legend.key.width = unit(3, "cm"),
      legend.text = element_text(size = 10, color = "black"),
      legend.title = element_text(color = "black"),
      axis.text = element_blank(),
      axis.ticks = element_blank(),
      axis.title = element_blank(),
      panel.grid = element_blank()
    )
}
options(repr.plot.width = 12, repr.plot.height = 9)
